role_process_mappings.col_4: 6.4.2 Stakeholder needs and requirements definition process:
role_process_mappings.col_5: Prepare the stakeholder needs and requirements definition process
role_process_mappings.col_6: The requirements of the stakeholders should be identified. To do this, all stakeholders must first be identified and then their requirements for the system.
The implementation is planned by developing an implementation strategy, i.e. defining which manufacturing process will be used, which tools and manufacturing tolerances will be selected.
An integration strategy is developed. Test tools and equipment for the integration are reserved.
Verification activities and associated roles and responsibilities are planned.
Installation procedure/ a handover strategy is drawn up. Content for operator training, logistics support, delivery and troubleshooting/problem solving must be developed.
A maintenance strategy is developed. Spare parts stocks are monitored and trained maintenance personnel are coordinated.
The disposal strategy is planned and the concept is assessed.

incose_competencies.field_3: Core competencies support both engineering and systems engineering.
incose_competencies.field_5: The competence to apply fundamental concepts of systems thinking in systems engineering.
The ability to select the right lifecycles during the realization of a system.
The ability to understand what role the SOI plays in an overall system of which it is a part.
The presence of basic skills in math, science, engineering and related tools/applications.
The ability to objectively analyze and evaluate a topic in order to form an opinion about it.
The ability to provide accurate data and information using models to support technical understanding and decision making.
Ability to communicate constructively, efficiently and consciously
Humane and fair organization of the relationship between employees and superiors
The ability to select appropriate goals for an SOI and achieve them with a team
Negotiation skills combine the components of technical skills, methodological skills, personal skills, management skills, social skills, leadership skills and action skills.
Ability to strengthen a team's cohesion, creativity and efficiency. Leads by example.
The ability to support others in solving problems without solving the problem themselves.
Is the ability to recognize one's own feelings and those of other people, to classify them correctly and to derive actions from them.
Is able to encourage individual employees to "do things right" and "do the right things". Goals can thus be better analyzed and achieved.

incose_competencies.field_3: Ability to perform tasks primarily associated with a series of technical processes.
incose_competencies.field_5: Analyzing the needs and expectations of stakeholders to define the requirements for a system

The definition of system structure,
interfaces and the associated derived requirements to develop an implementable solution.
Ensuring that the requirements of all lifecycle phases are addressed in the right place in the system design.
The logical process of assembling a set of system elements and aggregates into the realized system, product or service
The identification, definition and control of interactions across system or system element boundaries
A formal process for obtaining objective proof that a system fulfills its specified requirements and properties.
A formal process for obtaining objective evidence that the system achieves its intended use in the intended operating environment
Integration of a tested system into its operating environment
When the system is in operation, its capabilities/functionalities are maintained over its lifetime.

incose_competencies.field_3: The ability to perform the tasks necessary to monitor and manage systems engineering activities.
incose_competencies.field_5: The ability to create, coordinate and review effective workable interdisciplinary plans
The ability to evaluate ongoing projects to ensure that plans are still achievable and appropriate.
The ability to identify, characterize and evaluate an objective set of alternatives in a structured and analytical manner.
The ability to parallelize working methods and tasks
The ability to consider the needs and requirements of other internal stakeholders during system development.
The ability to deliver/receive a product or service according to requirements
The ability to address all aspects of information for specific stakeholders in order to deliver the right information at the right time and with the right level of certainty.
The ability to harmonize system functions, performance and physical characteristics over the lifecycle and ensure consistency.
The ability to identify and minimize uncertain events or maximize the potential of uncertain events.

incose_competencies.field_3: The competence group recognizes systems engineering as an integrating discipline that brings together the activities, experience and thinking of specialists from other disciplines to create a whole.
incose_competencies.field_5: The ability to identify, plan and coordinate activities to deliver a satisfactory system, product or service of appropriate quality.
The ability to calculate and track costs associated with the project.
The ability to support and maintain a product that has been delivered to the end user.
The ability to achieve customer satisfaction by controlling key product features.

incose_competencies.field_3: The ability to successfully manage and execute projects and product development in an agile environment
incose_competencies.field_5: The ability to organize oneself.
The ability to deal with and help shape change and transformation. The ability to adopt and learn new methods, ways of thinking, skills, etc.
The ability to apply methods that support the agile values in the project context
The competence to know who you are, to recognize where you want to go and the ability to proactively work towards achieving your goals.
